    "extras": [
      "June–September is the practical season for this exact loop; many Terelj, Gobi and Khövsgöl ger camps simply do not operate outside that window.",
      "Carry plenty of cash in MNT once you leave Ulaanbaatar because card terminals and ATMs are unreliable in the countryside.",
      "A hired 4WD with driver is essential for Karakorum and the Gobi even if you are comfortable on rough roads; self-drive visitors struggle with fuel logistics, washboards and route finding.",
      "Domestic flights on MIAT and other local carriers have strict baggage allowances, so keep one soft duffel for road legs and one smaller flight bag.",
      "The Trans-Mongolian railway is excellent for extending the trip from Ulaanbaatar to Russia or China, but it is not a substitute for the jeep-and-flight network needed for Mongolia’s classic countryside highlights."
    ],
